    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD is a superlative example of lightweight, front-midship engineering. It features the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine with its factory-original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, delivering seamless boost across the powerband. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The chassis remains stock and unmolested, preserving the surgical feedback of the four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and 50/50 weight distribution. Mechanically, this vehicle is impeccable; the cooling system\u2014a critical point for rotaries\u2014has been proactively serviced, and the vacuum-operated control system for the turbos functions with factory accuracy. With zero structural oxidation and a cabin that shows no UV degradation, this FD is a collector-grade specimen that performs exactly as Hiroshima intended.",
